<bibRefCitation author="Jong, S. C. &amp; Davis, E. E." box="[303,541,1855,1881]" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" pagination="1351 - 1356" refId="ref5627" refString="Jong, S. C. &amp; Davis, E. E. (1972) Phialocephala humicola, a new hyphomycete. Mycologia 64 (6): 1351 - 1356. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.1972.12019390" type="journal article" year="1972">Jong &amp; Davis (1972)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1855,2061]" lastBlockId="6.[136,1451,158,221]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="73" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">
Notes:— 
<taxonomicName box="[290,564,1891,1917]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Mollisiaceae" genus="Phialocephala" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="humicola">
<emphasis box="[290,564,1891,1917]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Phialocephala humicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was initially reported as saprophytes on soil in 
<collectingRegion box="[1089,1219,1891,1917]" country="United States of America" name="New Jersey" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">New Jersey</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1229,1283,1891,1917]" name="United States of America" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Jong, S. C. &amp; Davis, E. E." pageId="5" pageNumber="72" pagination="1351 - 1356" refId="ref5627" refString="Jong, S. C. &amp; Davis, E. E. (1972) Phialocephala humicola, a new hyphomycete. Mycologia 64 (6): 1351 - 1356. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.1972.12019390" type="journal article" year="1972">Jong &amp; Davis 1972</bibRefCitation>
). Although we did not isolate the 
<typeStatus box="[581,629,1927,1953]" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">type</typeStatus>
strains, we have examined the DNA sequence data from ex-type culture and another culture deposited under that species name in GenBank. Multi-locus phylogenetic analyses indicate that this species formed a well-supported monophyletic lineage in 
<taxonomicName box="[849,978,1999,2025]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Chaetosphaeriaceae" genus="Chloridium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chaetosphaeriales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[849,978,1999,2025]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Chloridium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and can be differentiated from the other species in 
<taxonomicName box="[257,386,2035,2061]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Chaetosphaeriaceae" genus="Chloridium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chaetosphaeriales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[257,386,2035,2061]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Chloridium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its morphological characteristics and DNA sequence data (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1165,2035,2061]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1824,1846]" captionTargetBox="[199,1408,886,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-270@3.[151,1436,868,1796]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phylogram of RAxML analysis based on a combined ITS and LSU sequence dataset within Chloridium. Adautomilanezia caesalpiniae was used as outgroup. Bootstrap support values for Maximum likelihood and Maximum parsimony greater than 50%, and Bayesian posterior probabilities equal to or greater than 0.8 are indicated at the nodes (ML/BI/MP). Type strains are highlighted by a “*”, and our strain is in bold." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605363" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605363/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Fig 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1181,1198,2035,2061]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1227,1249]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,224,1184]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[151,1436,190,1203]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Splitgraphs showing the results of the pairwise homoplasy index (PHI) test of newly described taxa and closely related species using both LogDet transformation and splits decomposition. PHI test results (Φw) &lt;0.05 indicate significant recombination within the dataset. Type strains and new taxa are indicated with “*” and bold, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605365" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605365/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">2</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Jong, S. C. &amp; Davis, E. E." box="[1212,1439,2035,2061]" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" pagination="1351 - 1356" refId="ref5627" refString="Jong, S. C. &amp; Davis, E. E. (1972) Phialocephala humicola, a new hyphomycete. Mycologia 64 (6): 1351 - 1356. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.1972.12019390" type="journal article" year="1972">Jong &amp; Davis 1972</bibRefCitation>
). Based on morphological characters and phylogenetic analyses, we therefore transferred 
<taxonomicName box="[1123,1255,158,184]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Mollisiaceae" genus="Phialocephala" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="73" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="humicola">
<emphasis box="[1123,1255,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="73">P. humicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName box="[1292,1421,158,184]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Chaetosphaeriaceae" genus="Chloridium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chaetosphaeriales" pageId="6" pageNumber="73" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1292,1421,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="73">Chloridium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new combination.
</paragraph>
